text.section:
An antiarson application shall include:
the name and address of the applicant, any mortgagee, and any other party with an ownership interest in the property to be insured;
the amount of insurance requested and the method of valuation used to establish that amount;
the dates and selling prices of the property to be insured in all real estate transactions involving the property during the 3-year period immediately preceding the date of the antiarson application;
the applicant's history of losses during the 5-year period immediately preceding the date of the antiarson application with regard to any property:
in which the applicant held an interest, including a partnership or mortgage interest, that is substantial; and
that sustained a fire loss exceeding 25% of the insured value;
all taxes that are unpaid or overdue for 1 or more years; and
the present occupancy of the property to be insured.
